{
  "answer": "**The Parāśara Smṛti positions itself as the authoritative *dharmaśāstra* (text on righteous duties and law) specifically for the Kali *yuga* (current cosmic age of decline), including its rules on *prāyaścitta* (expiations or penances).**[^1][^2]\n\nIn Chapter 1, Parāśara declares that while *dharmas* vary by *yuga* (with his own applying to Kali), \"the *prāyaścitta* prescribed by Parāśara is also ordained\" as valid across contexts.[^3] This text thus supplies the specific, simplified expiations suited to Kali *yuga*'s moral decay—contrasting stricter rules from prior ages (e.g., Manu's for Kṛta *yuga*.[^4]\n\nDetailed *prāyaścitta* rules appear primarily in Chapters 9–12, prescribing penances like *Kṛcchra*, *Cāndrāyaṇa*, *Prājāpatya*, *Taptakṛcchra*, and *Atikṛcchra* (with graduated severity by *varṇa* [social class], e.g., for killing cows,[^5] sexual misconduct,[^6] impure food,[^7] or bathing rites[^8]). Examples:\n- Eating impure food (e.g., cow flesh): *dvija* [*twice-born*: Brāhmaṇa, Kṣatriya, Vaiśya] performs full *Kṛcchra* + *Cāndrāyaṇa*; Śūdra does *Prājāpatya*.[^9]\n- Intercourse with forbidden woman: *Cāndrāyaṇa*.[^10]\n\nNo other single verse isolates \"prayascittas in Kali\" beyond this framework; the corpus lacks it elsewhere. These are \"common rules... for the four *varṇas*\" in Kali.[^11]\n\n[^1]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-d9b4b0](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-d9b4b0).\n[^2]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-121575](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-121575).\n[^3]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-a0d99c](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-a0d99c).\n[^4]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-121575](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-121575).\n[^5]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 9 (e.g., full vow for killing; fractions for injury), [p-c87bbd](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/09/translation/#p-c87bbd).\n[^6]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 10 (e.g., *Cāndrāyaṇa* for *agamyāgamana*), [p-2b9a87](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/10/translation/#p-2b9a87).\n[^7]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 11 (e.g., *Brahmakūrca* for tainted vessels), [p-b50cf8](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/11/translation/#p-b50cf8).\n[^8]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 12 (e.g., types of purifying baths), [p-0b72ec](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/12/translation/#p-0b72ec).\n[^9]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 11, [p-b50cf8](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/11/translation/#p-b50cf8).\n[^10]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 10, [p-2b9a87](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/10/translation/#p-2b9a87).\n[^11]: Parāśara Smṛti, Chapter 1, [p-026cf5](/works/unknown-parasara-smrti-2259be/01/translation/#p-026cf5).",
